After an agent raises a PR (PRD-015, OR-R080), it enters the priority loop:

```python
def priority_loop(agent):
    # 1. Fix own PR comments
    own_prs = get_prs_with_comments(agent)
    if own_prs:
        return Action("fix_comments", own_prs[0])

    # 2. Merge own approved PR
    approved_prs = get_approved_prs(agent)
    if approved_prs and merge_queue_allows(approved_prs[0]):
        return Action("merge", approved_prs[0])

    # 3. Review others' PRs
    review_assignments = get_review_assignments(agent)
    if review_assignments:
        return Action("review", review_assignments[0])

    # 4. Pick next task or wait
    next_task = get_next_available_task()
    if next_task:
        return Action("start_task", next_task)

    return Action("idle")
```

The priority loop is evaluated by the Ollama Team Lead (OR-R081) to avoid spending paid tokens on status checking. The Team Lead runs this evaluation every 30 seconds (or on event triggers like PR approval, review comment, merge completion).
